headline: Despite Medicaid Pressure, Elevance Health Delivers Strong Q1 Performance, Reiterates Profit Outlook
summary: Elevance Health Inc. (NYSE:ELV) on Tuesday reported first-quarter 2025 revenues of $48.77 billion, up 15% year-over-year, higher than the consensus of $46.29 billion. The increase was driven by higher premium yields in the Health Benefits segment, acquisitions completed in the past year, Medicare Advantage and Individual ACA membership growth, and CarelonRx product revenue, partially offset by membership attrition in Medicaid business. headline: Elevance Health’s (NYSE:ELV) Q1 Sales Top Estimates
summary: Health insurance provider Elevance Health (NYSE:EVH) reported revenue ahead of Wall Street’s expectations in Q1 CY2025, with sales up 14.5% year on year to $48.77 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $11.97 per share was 4.3% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Elevance reports lower-than-expected medical costs, confirms profit beat
summary: Elevance also reiterated its full-year profit forecast of $34.15 to $34.85 per share, and confirmed first-quarter adjusted shareholders' net income of $11.97 per share on Tuesday.  Analysts had expected a quarterly profit of $11.38 per share.  The company had come out with preliminary earnings numbers last week, amid a sharp stock selloff in the sector after UnitedHealth, which runs the country's largest health insurer, missed quarterly profit estimates due to elevated patient care costs in its Medicare Advantage business.
